content.description: Start up thin face climbing just right of the chockstone.  Once established on the wall, continue up to the right across the arete and trend right to the anchors.
content.location: Starts just right of the large chockstone at the upper level of the Jungle Gym.

climbs.name: Put It In the Ting Ting

content.description: Start just left and up from of Gorilla Tactics.  Climb the crack feature making easy moves for the first few bolts, then step right and pull through amazing pockets and a slightly awkward topout.
content.location: next route left from Gorilla Tactics

content.description: This short little mediocre route offers some thin slabbing and a few bigger pulls on steeper terrain up high.  Looked like the best 5.10 warmup at the Jungle Gym.
content.location: First route before the rope ladder at the Jungle Gym.  To the right is "Bungle in the Jungle", then the rope ladder.

content.description: Follow the slab crack up to the roof.  Figure out how to pull through using finger locks, hand jams, knee bars, or all of the above.  Snag a nice chimney rest before cruising to the chains.  This is a reasonable warm up for the routes in the main overhanging face of the Jungle Gym.
content.protection: 9 bolts to chain and open shut anchor
content.location: Left of the main overhang.  Follow the chalk and bird shit stains out the short roof.

content.description: Gorilla Tactics is the most obvious line on the wall.  Start on some steep big holds and clip two bolts, then enter the crux to a good stance and head slightly right into another crux.  Finish on great jug pockets.
content.location: Heads straight up the main wall.  Look for the obvious "hole" hold above the second or third bolt.
